&lt;p>Email is the backbone of digital communication — yet most people hand their entire inbox to Gmail, Outlook, or Yahoo. That means &lt;strong>Google reads every email you send&lt;/strong>, Microsoft scans your attachments for advertising signals, and your metadata becomes a commodity sold to brokers.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>AdGuard Home vs Pi-hole: DNS Ad Blocking Comparison 2026</title><link>https://hopkdj.github.io/openswap-guide/posts/adguard-home-vs-pihole/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://hopkdj.github.io/openswap-guide/posts/adguard-home-vs-pihole/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="why-block-ads-at-the-dns-level">Why Block Ads at the DNS Level?&lt;/h2>
